==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interclude
<hw>In`ter*clude"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Intercluded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Intercluding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>intercludere</ets>,
<ets>interclusum</ets>; <ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>claudere</ets>
to shut. See <er>Close</er>, and cf. <er>Interclose</er>.]</ety> <def>To
shut off or out from a place or course, by something intervening; to
intercept; to cut off; to interrupt.</def>
<rj><au>Mitford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So all passage of external air into the receiver may be
<qex>intercluded</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interclusion</ent>⟦br⟧
